comment: [Observable in enhanced video] Green (GSW) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with Irving (CLE) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Irving (CLE) cleanly strips the ball away from Green (GSW).
Green (GSW) makes incidental contact with Irving (CLE) during the loose ball.
Korver (CLE) makes contact to Durant's (GSW) arm that affects his SQBR.
Thompson (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Durant (GSW) that does not affect his SQBR.
Love (CLE) sets the screen on Curry (GSW) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Curry (GSW) legally contests Korver's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
James (CLE) allows Durant (GSW) to land following the jump shot attempt.
Green (GSW) clears the lane within three seconds.
Thompson (GSW) allows Irving (CLE) to land following the jump shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] RATR shows that Curry (GSW) moves his pivot foot.
RATR shows Irving (CLE) make incidental contact with Curry (GSW) that does not affect his SQBR.
Korver (CLE) commits a take foul on Durant (GSW).
Iguodala (GSW) legally contests James' (CLE) jump shot attempt and cleanly makes contact with the ball.
James (CLE) grabs Iguodala's (GSW) shoulder and affects his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
James (CLE) is out of bounds when he makes contact with the ball.
Irving (CLE) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
LATR and RATR show Durant (GSW) make contact to Love's (CLE) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Love's (CLE) shot attempt hits the shot clock.
